      <BlogCrossLinks title="Scrabble Board Edges Strategy" />
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Board Edges Strategy — Mastering Side Lanes and Corner Plays</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>6 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔍</span> Solver</a> <a href="/activities/#quiz" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎯</span> Quiz</a> <a href="/activities/#anagram" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔀</span> Anagram</a> <a href="/activities/#rack" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Rack</a> <a href="/activities/#wotd" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> WOTD</a> <a href="/sixty-seconds/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">⏱️</span> 60s</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Most players focus on the centre of the board, but the edges hold the game's most powerful squares — all eight Triple Word Scores sit on the perimeter. Mastering edge play means controlling access to these premium positions while denying your opponent the same opportunity.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 TWSs</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">All on edges</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3× score</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Corner bonus</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1 direction</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Hook limit</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4 corners</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Premium targets</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why Edge Play Matters</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎯 TWS Access</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">All Triple Word Score squares sit on rows 1, 8, 15 or columns A, H, O — the perimeter</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🛡️ Defensive Strength</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Edge words can only be hooked from one side — your opponent has fewer extension options</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔒 Corner Control</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Using a corner TWS denies it permanently — no one else can score there</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📐 Board Containment</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Playing edges keeps the board tight, limiting your opponent's space for bingos</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Side Lane Tactics</h2>
      <p>Side lanes are the rows and columns running along the board's perimeter. Here's how to use them effectively:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Build towards TWS deliberately:</span> Place a mid-length word that ends 1-2 squares before a TWS. Next turn, extend through the TWS with a high-value letter for triple scoring.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Block opponent's edge access:</span> If your opponent is building towards a corner TWS, place a word perpendicular to their approach lane. This blocks their path without opening a new one.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Short words on DLS edge squares:</span> The edge DLS squares (Double Letter Score) are safer than centre ones because opponents can only approach from one direction. Place J, Q, X, Z tiles here.</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Corner Play Strategies</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 Offensive Corner</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Play a 7-letter word through the corner TWS for triple word + bingo bonus. Even a 10-point word triples to 30 + 50 bonus = 80 points.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🚫 Defensive Corner</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">If you can't reach the corner profitably, block it with a low-scoring word. Better you use it for 15 points than your opponent uses it for 45.</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">When to Play the Edges vs Centre</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">Leading</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">→ edges (contain)</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">Behind</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">→ centre (open)</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">High tiles</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">→ edges (TWS)</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">Bingo rack</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">→ centre (space)</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">Endgame</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">→ edges (control)</span></span>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The edges are <span class="text-white font-medium">the defensive player's territory</span>. When you're ahead, push play towards the perimeter — it limits bingo lanes, protects your lead, and gives you first access to Triple Word Scores. When you're behind, keep the centre open for comeback bingos.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/defensive-scrabble-strategy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Defensive Scrabble Strategy</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/blocking-triple-word-squares/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Blocking Triple Word Squares</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-board-control-strategy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Board Control Strategy</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔍 Find the perfect edge play for your tiles — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
